{"word":"δεῦρο","slug":"δεῦρο","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>δεῦρο</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> complex] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adv.\">adv.</a> The basic idea is position in the presence of the speaker with focus on immediacy; hence temporality and peremptoriness are related aspects <b><i>come!</i> <a href='B:470 19:21'>Mt 19:21</a>; <a href='B:500 11:43'>J 11:43</a>; <a href='B:510 7:3'>Ac 7:3</a>, <a href='B:510 7:34'>34</a>; <a href='B:730 17:1'>Rv 17:1</a>.</b> Of time <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ art.\">art.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἄχρι\">ἄχρι</a> τοῦ δ.</el> <i>until now</i> <b><a href='B:520 1:13'>Ro 1:13</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:δεσπότης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:δεῦτε\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}